licensing trust
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an elected body set up to sell alcoholic liquor and to distribute the profits to worthy causes.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: The Licensing Trusts Act, 1949, seems to be the relevant Act, although the Invercargill Trust seems to have been already in existence [see NZEF Times cit below].
Citations
Date: 0/0/1944
Source: NZ Statutes
Author:
Vol / Page: 1944/4 : 19
Edition:
Quote: This Act may be cited as the Invercargill Licensing Trust Act, 1944... There is hereby established for the purposes of this Act, a Trust, to be called the Invercargill Licensing Trust. Ibid. 1944/4  23 The functions of the Trust shall be to provide accommodation and other facilities for the travelling public within the Invercargill Licensing District, to establish and maintain hotels and suitable places within the district for the sale or supply of refreshments, to sell and supply intoxicating liquor within the district and establish and maintain premises for that purpose.. and to do all such other acts and things as may in the opinion of the Trust be necessary or desirable having regard to the general purposes of this Act.
